    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Named</td>
        <td>more than 140 colors</td>
        <td></td>
        <td> cornflowerblue</td>
        <td>The color keywords all represent plain, solid colors without transparency</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Hexadecimal</td>
        <td>Hex is a number system that has 16 digits, 0 to 9 followed by “A” to “F”</td>
        <td>Begin with # and specify values of red, blue, and green using hex numbers</td>
        <td>#23F41A</td>
        <td>Six-digit hex values with duplicate values for each RGB value can be shorted to 3 digits</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>RGB</td>
        <td>RGB colors have one value each for red, blue, and green</td>
        <td>rgb() with 3 values</td>
        <td>rgb(7, 210, 50)</td>
        <td>Values range from 0 to 255</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>HSL</td>
        <td>HSL stands for hue (the color itself), saturation (intensity), and lightness (light/dark)</td>
        <td>Hue ranges from 0 to 360 and saturation and lightness are both represented as percentages</td>
        <td>hsl(200, 20%, 50%)</td>
        <td></td>
      </tr>
<tr>
        <td>Opacity</td>
        <td>Can add opacity to color in RGB and HSL by adding a fourth value, A (alpha)</td>
        <td>Represented as a number (from 0 to 1) or a percentage where 1 is 100% opacity</td>
        <td>rgba(255, 255, 255, .5)</td>
        <td></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
